    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 522.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    552, of the 11th ultimo, in relation to the case of George Webber, a naturalized
                    American citizen who died in prison at Brusa, and to approve your note upon the
                    subject to the Porte.</p>
                <pb facs="0537" n="1271" xml:id="pg_1271"/>
                <p>The meagerness of the information procured is regretted, although it makes out a
                    prima facie case of cruelty, neglect, and violation of the treaty rights of an
                    American citizen. It is desired that an effort be made through the German
                    embassy at Constantinople to obtain the names and addresses of the two Germans
                    said to have been arrested and put in chains with Webber.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
